  "text": "The grazing treatment conducted during 2006 to 2010 was described in detail by [CITATION_1] . Two adult Tibetan sheep were fenced in each of the grazing plots on 7 July and 23 August 2010. The cumulative forage utilization rates were 55.5% for the NWG treatment and 57.7% for the WG treatment, respectively. The percentage of vegetation removed corresponded roughly to a moderate grazing/stocking rate for the study region. In 2011, there was no grazing during summer.",
